  "body": "I'm trying to display a data array in a table for which one property is also an array. When listing the table, only the last entry in that sub-array is displayed in the column for that property. I want to make it that when a table entry is clicked, it toggles an expanded version where there are rows added for each entry of that sub-array. Since the other columns will have the same value, I want to take advantage of the rowspan attribute.\n\nBoth representations work really well for an initial render (`state.expanded = false` and `state.expanded = true`), but it starts acting up when I try to toggle that state dynamically: http://jsfiddle.net/EzY3z/1/\n",
